A parser for CSS files
======================

FILES
-----

    css.wi:     the CSS grammar, a slightly modified version of the grammar
                found at
                http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/grammar.html

    scanner.py: a naive (not very efficient) implementation
                of the tokenizing rules from
                http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/grammar.html

    readcss.py: sligthly edited version of the "wisent -e" output

USAGE
-----

To run this example, first generate the parser:

    wisent -o parser.py css.wi

and then run the main program as follows:

    ./readcss.py <somefile.css>
